abstract: >
  An implementation-neutral benchmark specification and evaluation protocol for safety,
  guardrails, and user experience in multi-turn healthcare AI agent conversations. Defines
  a controlled A0-A4 ablation in which five agent variants differing by a declared
  capability bundle are scored over identical simulated conversations with synthetic
  personas, holding model, temperature, and seed constant. Scoring spans six Likert
  dimensions and two binary dimensions, with separate single-turn and multi-turn safety
  and escalation judges and a hard-fail override on missed escalation. Ships tier
  configurations, judge prompts, scoring anchors, a machine-readable scenario schema with
  hidden ground truth, a synthetic persona schema, and a reproducible dataset build
  pipeline. The reference runner and judge calibration set are forthcoming; scores
  produced before calibration are indicative, not validated measurement. Companion
  instrument to the SAFE-CARE framework for healthcare AI agent design and evaluation.
keywords:
  - healthcare AI
  - AI agents
  - evaluation
  - benchmark
  - ablation study
  - LLM-as-judge
  - guardrails
  - safety
  - multi-turn dialogue
  - retrieval-augmented generation
